---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
const ENTITY = 'Siterra';
---

<Legal title="Privacy Policy" updated="June 12, 2026" path="/privacy" description="How Siterra collects, uses, and protects the information you share — including form submissions, checkout details handled by Stripe, and your rights.">
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how {ENTITY} ("we", "us") collects, uses, and protects
    information when you use {SITE.domain} and our services.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information you provide directly, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Contact details — name, email, phone number, and business name</li>
    <li>Project details — your business type, service area, current website, and goals</li>
    <li>Payment information — processed securely by Stripe; we do not store full card numbers</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may also collect limited technical information automatically, such as general usage data, if
    analytics are enabled on the site.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use your information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to inquiries and prepare your Site Blueprint or quote</li>
    <li>To deliver, manage, and support the services you purchase</li>
    <li>To process payments and send transactional emails such as receipts and project updates</li>
    <li>To improve our services and communicate important changes</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we share information</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information. We share it only with service providers who help us
    operate — such as Stripe for payments, our hosting and email providers, and analytics tools you
    approve — and only as needed to deliver our services or comply with the law.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep your information for as long as needed to provide our services and meet legal and
    accounting obligations. You may request deletion of your personal information at any time, subject
    to records we are required to retain.
  </p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <p>
    You can request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal information by emailing us.
    You can also opt out of non-essential communications at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable measures to protect your information, including secure form handling and
    encrypted payment processing. No method of transmission over the internet is completely secure,
    however, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Material changes will be reflected by the "last
    updated" date above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions or requests about your privacy? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
  </p>
</Legal>
